name: Half-Steppin' w/ Snoop Dogg
description:
"Half-Steppin" is a dynamic remix that seamlessly blends the unique charismatic energy of an immersing artist with the iconic talents + experience of a rap legend. But what makes this collaboration truly special isn't just the music itself; it's the revolutionary power of Web3 technology that brought this masterpiece to life allowing fans to not just be listeners, but stakeholders in the artists' success.

"Half-Steppin" isn't just a song; it's a lifestyle. When you go after something, you have to go big or go home. If you half-step, it means you aren't giving your all. This is a reminder to always keep going no matter the circumstances and never half-step, or you'll only shrink your potential to reach your greatness

name: MakersPlace
description:
In her 2011 Playboy cover and pictorial, Smirnoff told Playboy: "As a dancer I've always embraced my body. I'm trilled to show  off my strong, toned physique in the pages of Playboy and celebrate my sexiness. Sexy is the confident energy a person produces. Sexy is the comfortable feeling of being who you are. I am fearless and love the adrenaline rush."  Playboy Publisher Hugh Hefner called Smirnoff's pictorial "t". Smirnoff is best know for her 18 appearances 0n the television series, "Dancing With The Stars", which she won the the show's Season 13. She was photographed on the Sony movie lot's cabaret set for the 2011 movie "Burlesque". Smirnoff is a professional Ballroom Dancer, having won the US Nationals, The Dutch Open, the US National Professional Championship five times each, and was the only woman to reach the British Professional Finals with four different partners.
The photograph is one single 35mm frame. It is not a composite, nor was it retouched in Photoshop. The image was created with strobes to stop the action, and tungsten "hot lights" for the movement. The stage lights are incandescent light bulbs. The trick is to balance all the different types of light sources...their intensity and color balance as Karina dances across the dark stage.

name: okartwork
description:
On the day Daniel Dumile (aka MF DOOM) transitioned something strange came over me. I was sitting at my kitchen table, which doubled as my art desk, and this image started coming out of my hands.

Mind you, I had no idea he transitioned. Aside from our project together, I had no connections to him. When the world found out the news, which was around News Years of 2021, I still didn't put two and two together.

It wasn't until about a year later that an artist named Jimetta Rose made me aware that the painting and his transitioning happened the same day (possibly the same time). She saw my Instagram & Facebook posting of this painting and cross-referenced the dates.

I suddenly remembered how I felt that day and the energy that surrounded me. This is why the piece is called Soul of DOOM. I truly believe there is a connection somehow.

This painting comes with a link to the original .psd
